## Resetting and Adjusting State

### Reset All State - Use Keys
```javascript
// 🔴 BAD - resetting state in Effect
function ProfilePage({ userId }) {
  const [comment, setComment] = useState('');
  
  useEffect(() => {
    setComment('');
  }, [userId]);
}

// ✅ GOOD - use key to reset state
function ProfilePage({ userId }) {
  return <Profile userId={userId} key={userId} />;
}

function Profile({ userId }) {
  const [comment, setComment] = useState('');
}
```

**Rule**: To reset state when a prop changes, pass a unique `key` to make React treat it as a different component.

### Adjust Partial State - Calculate During Render
```javascript
// 🔴 BAD - adjusting state in Effect
function List({ items }) {
  const [selection, setSelection] = useState(null);
  
  useEffect(() => {
    setSelection(null);
  }, [items]);
}

// ✅ GOOD - store ID and calculate during render
function List({ items }) {
  const [selectedId, setSelectedId] = useState(null);
  const selection = items.find(item => item.id === selectedId) ?? null;
}
```

**Rule**: Store minimal state (IDs, not objects) and derive values during rendering.

