## DOM Manipulation with Refs

### Getting DOM Refs
```javascript
function Form() {
  const inputRef = useRef(null);
  
  function handleClick() {
    inputRef.current.focus();
  }
  
  return <input ref={inputRef} />;
}
```

### Ref Callbacks for Dynamic Lists
```javascript
// ✅ GOOD - ref callback for list
function CatFriends() {
  const itemsRef = useRef(null);
  
  function getMap() {
    if (!itemsRef.current) {
      itemsRef.current = new Map();
    }
    return itemsRef.current;
  }
  
  return (
    <ul>
      {items.map(item => (
        <li
          key={item.id}
          ref={(node) => {
            const map = getMap();
            map.set(item, node);
            return () => map.delete(item);
          }}
        />
      ))}
    </ul>
  );
}
```

### Passing Refs to Custom Components
```javascript
// ✅ GOOD - passing ref as prop
function MyInput({ ref }) {
  return <input ref={ref} />;
}

function Parent() {
  const inputRef = useRef(null);
  return <MyInput ref={inputRef} />;
}
```

### Limiting Exposed API with useImperativeHandle
```javascript
function MyInput({ ref }) {
  const realInputRef = useRef(null);
  
  useImperativeHandle(ref, () => ({
    focus() {
      realInputRef.current.focus();
    }
    // Only expose focus, not full DOM node
  }));
  
  return <input ref={realInputRef} />;
}
```

### DOM Manipulation Rules
1. **Avoid modifying DOM managed by React** - can cause crashes
2. **Safe to modify parts React doesn't touch**
3. **Use for non-destructive actions** (focus, scroll, measure)
4. **Never remove nodes React is managing**

```javascript
// 🔴 DANGEROUS - removing React-managed node
ref.current.remove();

// ✅ SAFE - focusing React-managed node
ref.current.focus();

// ✅ SAFE - modifying empty container React doesn't touch
emptyDivRef.current.appendChild(externalElement);
```

### flushSync for Synchronous DOM Updates
```javascript
import { flushSync } from 'react-dom';

function handleAdd() {
  flushSync(() => {
    setTodos([...todos, newTodo]);
  });
  // DOM is now updated, safe to scroll
  listRef.current.lastChild.scrollIntoView();
}
```

